documentType: evidence inventory and chain of custody form
summary: This document is an FBI evidence inventory (FD-1087) and chain of custody form (FD-192) for a box of seized items related to case 31E-MM-108062. It lists various message printouts and white papers identified by initials, and tracks the custody history of the evidence from its collection in 2006 to an inventory in 2021.

events.title: Evidence Collection
events.description: A box of evidence, including message printouts and white papers, was collected for case 31E-MM-108062.

events.title: Evidence Inventory
events.description: The evidence box was last inventoried, indicating ongoing custody and review of the materials.

keyFacts: The evidence relates to FBI case number 31E-MM-108062, which is an Epstein-related case identifier.

The seized materials include numerous 'MESSAGE PRINTOUTS' and 'WHITE PAPERS' identified by initials (e.g., C.J., M., P.S., A., J.L., T., J.H., G.D., M.M. H., C.W., S.B.), suggesting communications and documents from various individuals.
The evidence was collected on August 28, 2006, and was still in custody as of the last inventory on July 20, 2021.
The chain of custody form (FD-192) is incomplete without reference to the evidence inventory form (FD-1087), indicating standard evidence handling procedures.
The holding office for the evidence is listed as New York, NY.
